Chidiebube Okeoma, Owerri There was jubilation in Imo State on Monday as news broke that a combined team of policemen and soldiers had killed a wanted kidnapper cum armed robber, Chijioke Onyenze, popularly known as Bracket. A police source told our correspondent on Monday that Bracket who had been on the police wanted list for over a year was gunned down on Sunday at Obitti Rubber plantation forest during a gun duel. Recalled that Bracket and his gang had invaded a community in the oil rich Ohaji/Egbema Local Government Area and killed several people, including the president general of the community, a retired police officer. A community source identified as Iked, said, “We are excited that Bracket has met his Waterloo. He was a torn in our flesh .” A police source said “He came to Imo state from Omoku in Rivers State. When he noticed that a combined team of policemen and soldiers had closed in on him, he ran into the Obitti Rubber plantation forest and engaged us in a gun battle. When contacted the police spokesperson in the state, Orlando Ikeokwu, confirmed the development. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com 